<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 10:43PM CDT  by NWS New Orleans</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Harrison and central Hancock Counties through 1130 PM CDT...
At 1042 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pearlington, or 11 miles east of Slidell, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bay St. Louis, Waveland, Diamondhead, Kiln, Pearlington and Shoreline
Park.
This includes Interstate 10 in Mississippi between mile markers 1 and
26.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
